{
  "stem": "4345.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when we-- and my mommy said to her, Malka, you are going to get married to this boy, to Rolf Goldstein.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But she says, Mommy, I don't really love him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She said, Malka, love should not be now the-- the question because if you do have a husband, when the Germans come in, they will not touch a married woman.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And under this pretext-- I don't know if it was a pretext or Mommy really believed in what she said.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She probably believed, and my sister got married.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we already had her husband, and I think that she was already pregnant at that time because the baby came soon thereabout, I think, early December-- September, October, November, December.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The baby came some times later on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and in 1940, the baby came, I think.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the evacuation, less than about six weeks, we were-- So you were all on this train and how many wagons were there?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, there were so many families because at that time, everybody still lived in town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nobody was-- the Germans had not invaded our town, at least, yet.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the invasion had already taken place.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As I will go on, you'll see.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We started-- we went through [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Plaszow, ?] through-- through different towns, Krakow-- we passed the Vistula, that big river Vistula that falls into the-- to the Baltic Ocean.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was low tide at one point and we crossed it, believe it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were on the-- on the buggies and the older people, like my sister, my-- my dad, my mom, they would hold onto the-- to the-- to the carriage and the horses, which schlepped up.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
